segment.source: You can run an assessment to collect traces on one PC, and analyze the data on another PC or at another time.
segment.target: You can run an assessment to collect traces on one PC, and analyze the data on another PC or at another time.

segment.source: You might want to collect traces without analysis in order to:
segment.target: You might want to collect traces without analysis in order to:

segment.source: Run analysis on a PC with more memory or a faster processor
segment.target: Run analysis on a PC with more memory or a faster processor

segment.source: Delay analysis to free up time for other high priority uses of the machines
segment.target: Delay analysis to free up time for other high priority uses of the machines

segment.source: Run on a PC that already has symbols configured
segment.target: Run on a PC that already has symbols configured

segment.source: Reanalyze assessment data later with updated diagnostic modules or symbols
segment.target: Reanalyze assessment data later with updated diagnostic modules or symbols

segment.source: Collect the data on all devices, but analyze only those that meet specific criteria
segment.target: Collect the data on all devices, but analyze only those that meet specific criteria

segment.source: To collect trace files without running analysis
segment.target: To collect trace files without running analysis

segment.source: Select a job or assessment to run.
segment.target: Select a job or assessment to run.

segment.source: On the Configure job screen, select Collect traces only.
segment.target: On the Configure job screen, select Collect traces only.

segment.source: Run the job.
segment.target: Run the job.

segment.source: Trace files for the assessment will be saved to %UserProfile%DocumentsAssessment Results.
segment.target: Trace files for the assessment will be saved to %UserProfile%DocumentsAssessment Results.

segment.source: Note
segment.target: Note

segment.source: Collecting trace files without analysis is not available for all jobs and assessments.
segment.target: Collecting trace files without analysis is not available for all jobs and assessments.

segment.source: Run analysis on another device
segment.target: Run analysis on another device

segment.source: You can load symbols on the PC where you want to analyze trace files.
segment.target: You can load symbols on the PC where you want to analyze trace files.

segment.source: For more information, see Symbol Support.
segment.target: For more information, see Symbol Support.

segment.source: To run analysis on trace files using WAC
segment.target: To run analysis on trace files using WAC

segment.source: In the Windows Assessment Console, click Options, and then click Open Results to see all the job results that are available for viewing.
segment.target: In the Windows Assessment Console, click Options, and then click Open Results to see all the job results that are available for viewing.

segment.source: In the Select Results window, select the results that you want to analyze.
segment.target: In the Select Results window, select the results that you want to analyze.

segment.source: Click Open to open the results in details view.
segment.target: Click Open to open the results in details view.

segment.source: The Analysis complete row of the results shows False.
segment.target: The Analysis complete row of the results shows False.

segment.source: Click Analyze.
segment.target: Click Analyze.

segment.source: If you have multiple results open that can be analyzed, you can select which ones to analyze.
segment.target: If you have multiple results open that can be analyzed, you can select which ones to analyze.
